################################################################################
# To install in your home directory
################################################################################

If you do not have a $HOME/libs directory, you should make one. 
  
  mkdir $HOME/libs

Make a soft link in $HOME/libs to libs in youryour pydecay installation. 
For instance, if you have installed pydecay in your home directory, 

  ln -s $HOME/pydecay/pydecay $HOME/libs/

Add this soft link to your PYTHONPATH environment variable.

* In .cshrc 

  setenv PYTHONPATH $HOME/libs/:${PYTHONPATH}


